# Resources Pattern Guide

Generalized dashboard page creation system for rapid development of data management interfaces.

## Overview

The resources system provides a highly generalized pattern for creating dashboard pages with:
- Standardized table views with pagination
- Detail views with consistent field display
- Built-in filtering and search capabilities
- Content blocks for reusable display components
- GraphQL integration with progressive queries
- Separation between organization-level and admin-level resources

## File Structure & Organization

### Directory Layout

```
services/web/app/components/resources/
├── index.ts                    # Main resource registry (org-level)
├── admin/                      # Admin-only resources
│   ├── index.ts               # Admin resource registry 
│   ├── users.tsx              # Admin user management
│   ├── orgs.tsx               # Admin organization management
│   ├── api-keys.tsx           # Admin API key management
│   └── webhooks.tsx           # Admin webhook management
├── blocks/                     # Reusable content blocks
│   ├── index.tsx              # Core content blocks (CreatedAt, ID, etc.)
│   ├── user.tsx               # User-related content blocks
│   ├── org.tsx                # Organization-related content blocks
│   ├── api-keys.tsx           # API key-specific content blocks
│   ├── webhooks.tsx           # Webhook-specific content blocks
│   ├── members.tsx            # Membership-specific content blocks
│   └── [resource-name].tsx    # Resource-specific content blocks
├── api-keys.tsx               # Organization API keys
├── members.tsx                # Organization members
├── webhooks.tsx               # Organization webhooks
├── renders.tsx                # Video renders
├── isobmff-files.tsx          # Video files
├── unprocessed-files.tsx      # Uploaded files
├── image-files.tsx            # Image files
├── transcriptions.tsx         # Audio transcriptions
└── [other-resources].tsx     # Additional resources
```

### Resource Types

#### Organization-Level Resources
Located in `services/web/app/components/resources/[name].tsx`
- **Access Level**: `org-reader` or `org-admin` 
- **Scope**: Data scoped to user's organization
- **Examples**: api-keys, members, webhooks, renders, files

#### Admin-Level Resources  
Located in `services/web/app/components/resources/admin/[name].tsx`
- **Access Level**: `ef-admin` (system administrator)
- **Scope**: Cross-organization system management
- **Examples**: users, orgs, system-wide api-keys, webhooks

### Content Blocks System

Content blocks are reusable display components organized by domain:

#### Core Blocks (`blocks/index.tsx`)
Universal blocks used across all resources:
```typescript
export const CreatedAt: ContentBlock<{ created_at: string }>;
export const ID: ContentBlock<{ id: string }>;
export const StartedAt: ContentBlock<{ started_at: string | null }>;
export const CompletedAt: ContentBlock<{ completed_at: string | null }>;
export const FailedAt: ContentBlock<{ failed_at: string | null }>;
export const ExpiresAt: ContentBlock<{ expires_at: string | null }>;
```

#### Domain-Specific Blocks (`blocks/[domain].tsx`)
Specialized blocks for specific data types:

**User Blocks (`blocks/user.tsx`):**
```typescript
export const UserName: ContentBlock<{ first_name: string | null; last_name: string | null }>;
export const UserEmail: ContentBlock<{ email_passwords: { email_address: string }[] }>;
```

**Organization Blocks (`blocks/org.tsx`):**
```typescript
export const OrgName: ContentBlock<{ display_name: string }>;
export const OrgWebsite: ContentBlock<{ website: string | null }>;
export const OrgIsPaid: ContentBlock<{ is_paid: boolean | null }>;
export const OrgMembers: ContentBlock<{ memberships: MembershipData[] }>;
export const OrgMemberships: ContentBlock<{ memberships: { org: OrgData; role: string }[] }>;
```

**Resource-Specific Blocks (`blocks/api-keys.tsx`, `blocks/webhooks.tsx`, etc.):**
```typescript
// API Keys
export const Name: ContentBlock<{ name: string }>;
export const WebhookURL: ContentBlock<{ webhook_url: string | null }>;
export const ExpiresIn: ContentBlock<{ expired_at: string | null }>;

// Webhooks  
export const URL: ContentBlock<{ url: string }>;
export const Events: ContentBlock<{ events: string[] }>;
```

## Core Resource Structure

### Organization-Level Resource

```typescript
import { progressiveQuery } from "@/graphql.client";
import { graphql } from "@/graphql";
import type { ResourceView } from "~/components/resources";
import { CreatedAt, RelatedUser, RelatedOrg } from "~/components/resources/blocks";
import { SpecificBlock } from "~/components/resources/blocks/my-resource";

// Organization-scoped query
const IndexQuery = progressiveQuery(
  "org-reader", // or "org-admin" for admin features within org
  graphql(`
    query MyResources($orgId: uuid!, $limit: Int!, $offset: Int!, $where_clause: my_table_bool_exp) {
      org: orgs_by_pk(id: $orgId) {
        page_info: my_table_aggregate(where: $where_clause) {
          aggregate {
            count
          }
        }
        rows: my_table(
          where: $where_clause,
          order_by: {created_at: desc},
          limit: $limit,
          offset: $offset
        ) {
          id
          name
          status
          created_at
          # ... other fields
        }
      }
    }
  `)
);

const DetailQuery = progressiveQuery(
  "org-reader",
  graphql(`
    query MyResource($id: uuid!, $orgId: uuid!) {
      record: my_table(where: { org_id: { _eq: $orgId }, id: { _eq: $id } }) {
        id
        name
        status
        created_at
        # ... other fields
      }
    }
  `)
);

export const MyResources: ResourceView<typeof IndexQuery, typeof DetailQuery> = {
  index: {
    query: IndexQuery,
    TableHeader, // Optional header component
    buildWhereClause, // Optional filtering function
    columns: [
      { name: "Name", content: SpecificBlock },
      { name: "Created", content: CreatedAt },
      { name: "User", content: RelatedUser }
    ]
  },
  detail: {
    query: DetailQuery,
    fields: [
      { name: "Name", content: SpecificBlock },
      { name: "Created", content: CreatedAt, vertical: true }
    ]
  }
};
```

### Admin-Level Resource

```typescript
import { progressiveQuery } from "@/graphql.client";
import { graphql } from "@/graphql";
import type { ResourceView } from "~/components/resources/admin";
import { CreatedAt, ID } from "~/components/resources/blocks";
import { UserName, UserEmail } from "~/components/resources/blocks/user";
import { OrgMemberships } from "~/components/resources/blocks/org";

// System-wide admin query (no org scoping)
const IndexQuery = progressiveQuery(
  "ef-admin", // System administrator access
  graphql(`
    query AdminUsers($limit: Int!, $offset: Int!, $where_clause: users_bool_exp) {
      rows: users(
        where: $where_clause,
        order_by: {created_at: desc},
        limit: $limit,
        offset: $offset
      ) {
        id
        first_name
        last_name
        created_at
        email_passwords {
          email_address
        }
      }
    }
  `)
);

const DetailQuery = progressiveQuery(
  "ef-admin",
  graphql(`
    query AdminUser($id: uuid!) {
      record: users_by_pk(id: $id) {
        id
        first_name
        last_name
        created_at
        email_passwords {
          email_address
        }
        memberships {
          role
          org {
            display_name
          }
        }
      }
    }
  `)
);

export const Users: ResourceView<typeof IndexQuery, typeof DetailQuery> = {
  index: {
    query: IndexQuery,
    buildWhereClause,
    TableHeader: () => <Filter />,
    columns: [
      { name: "Name", content: UserName },
      { name: "Email", content: UserEmail },
      { name: "Joined", content: CreatedAt }
    ]
  },
  detail: {
    query: DetailQuery,
    fields: [
      { name: "ID", content: ID },
      { name: "Name", content: UserName },
      { name: "Email", content: UserEmail },
      { name: "Joined", content: CreatedAt },
      { name: "Memberships", content: OrgMemberships }
    ]
  }
};
```

## Content Blocks Development

### Creating Reusable Blocks

**Core Utility Blocks (`blocks/index.tsx`):**
```typescript
import type { ContentBlock } from "~/components/resources/blocks";

export const CreatedAt: ContentBlock<{ created_at: string }> = ({
  record: { created_at },
}) => <TimeAgoInWords date={created_at} />;

export const Status: ContentBlock<{ status: string }> = ({ 
  record: { status } 
}) => {
  const config = {
    success: { color: "text-green-600", bg: "bg-green-100" },
    error: { color: "text-red-600", bg: "bg-red-100" },
    pending: { color: "text-yellow-600", bg: "bg-yellow-100" }
  }[status] || { color: "text-gray-600", bg: "bg-gray-100" };
  
  return (
    <span className={clsx(
      "inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 rounded-md text-xs font-medium",
      config.color,
      config.bg
    )}>
      {status.charAt(0).toUpperCase() + status.slice(1)}
    </span>
  );
};
```

**Domain-Specific Blocks (`blocks/user.tsx`):**
```typescript
export const UserName: ContentBlock<{
  first_name: string | null;
  last_name: string | null;
}> = ({ record: { first_name, last_name } }) => (
  <span>
    {first_name ?? ""} {last_name ?? ""}
  </span>
);

export const UserEmail: ContentBlock<{
  email_passwords: { email_address: string }[];
}> = ({ record: { email_passwords } }) => (
  <span>
    {email_passwords?.map(({ email_address }) => email_address).join(", ")}
  </span>
);
```

**Resource-Specific Blocks (`blocks/api-keys.tsx`):**
```typescript
export const ExpiresIn: ContentBlock<{ expired_at: string | null }> = ({
  record: { expired_at },
}) => {
  if (!expired_at) {
    return <>Never expires</>;
  }

  const expirationDate = new Date(expired_at);
  const isExpired = expirationDate < new Date();

  if (isExpired) {
    return <>Expired</>;
  }

  return (
    <>
      Expires in <TimeAgoInWords date={expired_at} />
    </>
  );
};
```

### Complex Blocks with Tables

```typescript
export const OrgMembers: ContentBlock<{
  memberships: {
    role: string;
    user: {
      first_name: string | null;
      last_name: string | null;
      email_passwords: { email_address: string }[];
    };
  }[];
}> = ({ record: { memberships } }) => (
  <Table
    rows={memberships ?? []}
    emptyResultMessage="No members"
    rowKey={(member) =>
      `${member.user.email_passwords?.[0]?.email_address}-${member.role}`
    }
    columns={[
      {
        name: "Name",
        content: (member) => (
          <span>
            {member.user.first_name} {member.user.last_name}
          </span>
        ),
      },
      {
        name: "Email",
        content: (member) => member.user.email_passwords?.[0]?.email_address,
      },
      {
        name: "Role",
        content: (member) => member.role,
      },
    ]}
  />
);
```

## Resource Registration

### Organization Resources (`services/web/app/components/resources/index.ts`)

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";
// Import all organization-level resources
import { ApiKeys } from "./api-keys";
import { Members } from "./members";
import { Webhooks } from "./webhooks";
// ... other imports

export const ResourceType = z.enum([
  "api_keys",
  "members", 
  "webhooks",
  "renders",
  "isobmff_files",
  "unprocessed_files",
  "transcriptions",
  "image_files",
  // ... other org resources
]);

export const ResourceModules = {
  api_keys: ApiKeys,
  members: Members,
  webhooks: Webhooks,
  renders: Renders,
  isobmff_files: ISOBMFFFiles,
  unprocessed_files: UnprocessedFiles,
  transcriptions: Transcriptions,
  image_files: ImageFiles,
  // ... other mappings
} as const;
```

### Admin Resources (`services/web/app/components/resources/admin/index.ts`)

```typescript
import { z } from "zod";
// Import admin-specific resources  
import { Users } from "./users";
import { Orgs } from "./orgs";
import { ApiKeys } from "./api-keys";
// ... other imports

export const ResourceType = z.enum([
  "users",
  "orgs", 
  "api_keys",
  "webhooks",
  "image_files",
  "invites",
  // ... other admin resources
]);

export const ResourceModules = {
  users: Users,
  orgs: Orgs,
  api_keys: ApiKeys,
  webhooks: Webhooks,
  image_files: ImageFiles,
  invites: Invites,
  // ... other mappings  
} as const;
```

